#usda 1.0
(
    '''
    Ported from OpenUSD PCP test fixture
    testPcpMuseum_BasicPayloadDiamond.testenv/BasicPayloadDiamond/root.usda
    (Pixar OpenUSD release branch).

    Exercises the "payload diamond" configuration — /Root has payloads to
    both A and B, and A and B each payload C. Per spec §10.4 the four
    payload arcs compose without a cycle because no layer stack appears
    more than once along any single chain of includes; the diamond must
    not produce a cycle diagnostic, and C's opinions must be visible on
    /Root.

    Adaptation from upstream: the upstream fixture also defines a
    RootUnloaded prim exercising per-prim payload load state. nanousd
    has no notion of deferred payload loading (payloads compose eagerly),
    so only Root is ported.
    '''
)

def "Root" (
    payload = [ @./pcp_BasicPayloadDiamond_A.usda@</A>,
                @./pcp_BasicPayloadDiamond_B.usda@</B> ]
)
{
}
